def find_pairs(nums: list[int], target: int) -> list[tuple[int, int]]:
    seen: dict[int, list[int]] = {}
    pairs = []
    for j, x in enumerate(nums):
        need = target - x
        if need in seen:
            for i in seen[need]:
                pairs.append((i, j))
        seen.setdefault(x, []).append(j)
    return pairs
```

Single-pass hash-map approach: for each position, look up whether its complement has been seen earlier; O(n) time for the pairing logic.
